ood faith estimate for the\n5725-times of commencement and completion of the Cluster Study is [insert dates].\n5726-\n--\n6026-the short circuit, instability, and power flow issues identified in the Cluster Study.\n6027-\n6028-5.0\n6029-\n6030:The Interconnection Customer is providing a Commercial Readiness Deposit per Section\n6031-8.1 of this LGIP to enter the Interconnection Facilities Study and the greater of 25 percent\n6032-of the estimated cost of the Interconnection Facilities Study or $250,000.\n6033-The deposit shall be applied toward the cost of the Interconnection Facilities Study and\n6034-the development of this Interconnection Facilities Study Agreement and its attachment(s)\n--\n10567-Cluster Interconnection Facilities Study (\u201cCFAC\u201d) shall mean an Interconnection Facilities\n10568-Study performed using Clustering pursuant to Section 4.2.4.\n10569-Cluster Interconnection System Impact Study (\u201cCSIS\u201d) shall mean an Interconnection System\n10570-Impact Study performed using Clustering pursuant to Section 4.2.3.\n10571:CETU Participation Deposit shall mean a Commercial Readiness Deposit as described in\n10572-Section 4.2.\n10573-Cluster Request Window shall mean the time period set forth in Section 3.4.1 of this LGIP.\n10574-Cluster Restudy shall mean a restudy of a Cluster Study conducted pursuant to Section 7.5 of\n10575-this LGIP.\n--\n10597-generating electricity for sale, excluding electricity generated during Trial Operation.\n10598-Commercial Operation Date of a unit shall mean the date on which the Generating Facility\n10599-commences Commercial Operation as agreed to by the Parties pursuant to Appendix E to the Standard\n10600-Large Generator Interconnection Agreement.\n10601:Commercial Readiness Deposit shall mean a deposit paid as set forth in Sections 3.4.2, 4.4.2,\n10602-7.5, and 8.1 of this LGIP.\n10603-Confidential Information shall mean any confidential, proprietary or trade secret information of\n10604-a plan, specification, pattern, procedure, design, device, list, concept, policy or compilation relating to the\n10605-present or planned business of a Party, which is designated as confidential by the Party supplying the\n--\n10877-\n10878-Effective Date: 5/3/25 \u2013 ER25-2149-000\n10879-\n10880-\fRegulatory Limitations shall mean a federal, state, Tribal, or local law that makes it practically\n10881:infeasible to obtain Site Control within the time frame detailed in Section 3.4.2 of this LGIP.\n10882-Scoping Meeting shall mean the meeting between representatives of System Operator,\n10883-Interconnection Customer(s), Interconnecting Transmission Owner(s), or any Affected Party or Internal\n10884-Affected Party as deemed appropriate by the System Operator in accordance with applicable codes of\n10885-conduct and confidentiality requirements, conducted for the purpose of discussing the proposed\n--\n12862-require the Large Generating Facility to mitigate an Emergency Condition by taking\n12863-actions necessary and limited in scope to remedy the Emergency Condition, including,\n12864-but not limited to, directing Interconnection Customer to shut-down, start-up, increase or\n12865-decrease the real or reactive power output of the Large Generating Facility; implementing\n12866:a reduction or disconnection pursuant to Article 13.4.2; directing the Interconnection\n12867-Customer to assist with black start (if available) or restoration efforts; or altering the\n12868-outage schedules of the Large Generating Facility and the Interconnection Customer\u2019s\n12869-Interconnection Facilities. Interconnection Customer shall comply with all of System\n12870-\n--\n12874-Large Generating Facility real power and reactive power output within the\n12875-manufacturer\u2019s design limitations of the Large Generating Facility\u2019s equipment that is in\n12876-service and physically available for operation at the time, in compliance with Applicable\n12877-Laws and Regulations.\n12878:13.4.2 Red